# WebHawk — Cursor Project Rules
# C++ SaaS Security Middleware | Drogon Framework | Student 3 (Infrastructure)

---

## Project Stack
- Language: C++17
- Framework: Drogon (async HTTP — like Express.js but C++)
- Database: PostgreSQL (primary), Redis (rate limiting counters)
- Containers: Docker + Docker Compose

---

## Layered Architecture — MANDATORY
Every feature follows Route → Service → Repository. Never break this.

```
Route      = HTTP only. Parse request, call Service, return response. No SQL, no logic.
Service    = Business logic only. No HTTP, no raw SQL.
Repository = Database queries only. Returns domain objects.
```

**Bad:** SQL inside a route handler.  
**Bad:** HTTP response inside a repository.  
**Good:** Route calls Service, Service calls Repository.

---

## Directory Structure

```
webhawk/
├── middleware/src/
│   ├── routes/        ← HTTP handlers only
│   ├── services/      ← Business logic
│   ├── repositories/  ← DB queries
│   └── utils/         ← Stateless helpers (key gen, http forwarder)
├── vulnerable-backend/src/routes/
└── db/init.sql
```

