## Naming Conventions

```cpp
class PascalCaseClass {};
void camelCaseMethod();
std::string snake_case_variable;
constexpr std::string_view SCREAMING_SNAKE_CONSTANT = "value";
```

---

## Drogon Async Pattern — Always Use Callbacks, Never Block

```cpp
// CORRECT — async with callback
void ProxyService::forwardRequest(
    const drogon::HttpRequestPtr& req,
    std::function<void(const drogon::HttpResponsePtr&)>&& callback)
{
    auto client = drogon::HttpClient::newHttpClient(targetUrl_);
    client->sendRequest(req, [callback = std::move(callback)](
        drogon::ReqResult result,
        const drogon::HttpResponsePtr& response) {
        if (result == drogon::ReqResult::Ok) {
            callback(response);
        } else {
            auto err = drogon::HttpResponse::newHttpResponse();
            err->setStatusCode(drogon::k502BadGateway);
            callback(err);
        }
    });
}
```

---

## Drogon API Quick Reference

```cpp
// Reading a request
auto body    = req->getBody();
auto params  = req->getParameters();    // query string map
auto headers = req->getHeaders();
auto path    = req->getPath();
auto ip      = req->getPeerAddr().toIp();

// Sending responses
auto resp = drogon::HttpResponse::newHttpJsonResponse(jsonObject); // JSON
resp->setStatusCode(drogon::k200OK);
callback(resp);

auto resp = drogon::HttpResponse::newHttpResponse();              // plain
resp->setStatusCode(drogon::k403Forbidden);
resp->setBody(R"({"error":"Blocked by WebHawk"})");
callback(resp);

// Async DB query
auto db = drogon::app().getDbClient();
db->execSqlAsync(
    "SELECT * FROM backend_registration WHERE api_key = $1",
    [](const drogon::orm::Result& r) { /* success */ },
    [](const drogon::orm::DrogonDbException& e) { /* error */ },
    apiKey
);

// Filters (run before route handler — use for API key validation)
class ApiKeyFilter : public drogon::HttpFilter<ApiKeyFilter> {
public:
    void doFilter(const drogon::HttpRequestPtr& req,
                  drogon::FilterCallback&& fcb,
                  drogon::FilterChainCallback&& fccb) override;
};

// Smart pointers — never raw new/delete
auto repo = std::make_shared<BackendRepository>(dbClient_);
```

---

## Inter-Service Contract (Proxy → Security Engine)

Student 3's proxy calls Student 2's engine at `POST http://middleware:8081/api/security/scan`

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "ip": "1.2.3.4",
  "method": "POST",
  "path": "/api/users/login",
  "query_params": { "redirect": "..." },
  "headers": { "User-Agent": "..." },
  "body": "username=admin'--&password=x"
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{ "safe": false, "attack_type": "SQLi", "detail": "OR pattern in body" }
```

If `safe: true` → forward to real backend.  
If `safe: false` → return 403, log to `security_logs`.  
Always strip `X-WebHawk-API-Key` header before forwarding.

---

## Student 3 Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/backends/register` | Register backend, returns API key |
| GET | `/api/backends` | List registered backends |
| DELETE | `/api/backends/{id}` | Deactivate a backend |
| ANY | `/proxy/*` | Main proxy — inspect and forward everything |
